spanGrp.span: Me, I will tell a story
People were warring with each other and fighting over grazing land, that is, each person had their boundaries
gang'uch buneed gematoschew ndabojig yani barband is gawus diqandandany
'gàng''úch bùnééd gémàtòschèw ndàbòjíg yàní bàrbànd ìs gàwùs díqàndàndàny'
watu wanapigana vita na wanagombania ranchi yaani mtu anakuwa na mpaka wake
A Msukuma comes to herd in your area, and this thing a Datooga person doesn't like
gigon basukum aa gigabars dugwasch amagas datonyand ng'ashanj
'gìgòn bàsùkùm áà gígàbàrs dùgwàsch àmàgàs dàtónyànd ng''áshànj'
anakuja msukuma nakuchunga ndani ya malisho yako na hiyo kitu mdatoga hataki
A Datooga person is preparing his grazing land and a Msukuma goes to graze inside
qang'et datonyand aa gwasin ndabid dany qang'et basuk agigabars dugwasch
'qàng''ét dàtónyànd àà gwàsìn ndàbíd dány qàng''ét bàsúk àgígàbàrs dùgwásch'
mdatoga anajitengenezea ranchi yake naye msukuma anaenda kuchungia humo
And a Datooga doesn't want to see a Msukuma coming to graze in his area
amagas datonyad gidab giqon basukumajandaa qon qojeedaw hiji
àmàgàs dàtónyàd gídàb gíqòn bàsúkùmàjàndàà qòn qójéédàw hìjì
na mdatoga hataki kuona msukuma kuja kuchunga kwenye himaya yake
People were warring every day, but in the end the Datooga were finally defeated and others ran to Mang'ola
buneed gaqutosch galeg seeni aa imuch ejor datog aa gwasal aa qahid mang'ol
'bùnééd gàqútósch gàlég séénì àà ímùch éjòr dàtóg àà gwàsàl àà qàhìd màng''ól'
'watu wanapigana vita kila siku lakini mwisho wadatoga waliwezwa hatimaye wengine walikimbia mang''ola'
Those who didn't climb the hills
Others went to Musoma and others went to Ng'wakal.
surj gagal msoma aa surj gagal ng'wakalajeg
'súrj gàgál msòmà àà súrj gàgál ng''wàkàlàjég'
'wengine wakaelekea musoma na wengine wakaelekea ng''wakala'
Now these people they were fighting each other for grass and for the land
sasa fis gamatosch nyeg gamatosch ng'anyid
' sasa fís gàmàtósch nyég gàmàtósch ng''ànyíd'
sasa hao watu walikuwa wakigombania nyasi wanagombania nchi
Now people don't get along, people hate each other a lot
qamn buneed madgabarinyaj gayet buneed gosiday giyet
qàmn bùnééd màdgàbàrínyàj gàyét bùnééd gòsìdày gíyét
sasa hivi watu hawapendani watu wanachukiana sana
They are fighting every day and it doesn't end
This is how it is, people even now don't like each other, even now they are still warring with each other
ha gwasayin ha qamn buneed aa madgwadufch yani ar qamn buneed gad gabartosch ab gasheg gab ndabojig aa ng'asheg dus
'hà gwàsàyín hà qàmn bùnééd àà màdgwàdúfch yàní àr qàmn bùnééd gàd gàbàrtòsch àb ng''àshég gàb ndàbòjíg àà ng''àshég dùs'
ndiyo hivyo watu hata sasa hivi hawapendani hata sasa hivi bado wanapigana vita
A person doesn't like to see his neighbor's cowes
barband ida duw ab dahaji aa magasa
bàrbànd ídà dúw àb dàhàjí àà màgàsà
Even he sees the cows of that person, he doesn't like it because they will eat the grass of his cows
qwada gadni a magasa ad gid giqok nyeg jaqok sugesu
qwàdà gàdní à màgàsà àd gíd gíqòk nyég jàqòk súgésù
'akiona ng''ombe za huyo hataki kwa sababu atakula majani za ng''ombe wake'
Yes in the old days what people fought over was this
gwasin ha gid qay ng'utosches buneed
ndiyo zamani watu walichogombania ndiyo hicho
They were fighting, the Barabaig, the Asimjeeg, the Darorajeeg, the Gisamjanga, the Sukuma, all of them were fighting
buneed gebar emed emed barbayiga asmjeega aa darorajega aa gisamjanga a basukum yani gang'uch sen
'bùnééd gébàr éméd éméd bàrbàyígà àsmjéégà àà dàròràjégà àà gísàmjàngà à bàsúkùm yàní gàng''úch sén'
'halaiki ya watu walipigana wabarbayig waasmjeeg na wadarorajeg n''a gisamjangana wasukuma wote walikuwa wakipigana'
That is, people were fighting a lot
They were really fighting, until people were buried and the source especially was the grazing land
gabarj huma aa gabuny difo emed emed emed gabuny difo gematosch hanang'w indabojig
' gàbàrj húmà àà gàbúny dífò éméd éméd éméd gàbúny dífò gémàtòsch hànàng''w ìndàbójíg'
watu walipigana kweli hadi watu wakazikwa na katapila na chanzo hasa ni ranchi
Yeah, each person didn't want to see their neighbors
eeeh kila mtu hataki kumwona mwenzake
